result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jordin D Curry appeared by video.  Attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn in court for Jordin D Curry.  Prosecuting attorney Katie Bakunowicz for Mallory Davis in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Scheduling conference held. Defense requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. Any witness lists, special jury instructions, and motion in limine to be filed 48 hours before the final pretrial date. Court orders case adjourned for final pretrial and jury trial in Branch 29.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Jury trial scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jordin D Curry in court with attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Brett Olig - Village of Brown Deer Police Department.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 29.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jordin D Curry in court.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Status conference held.  Matter held via Zoom video conference and streamed through DAcast.  Court conducted Indigency Hearing. Court held colloquy with defendant. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by court. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. The court appointed Atty. Kerri Cleghorn, present in court, to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning at the completion of the case, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Signed, Distributed & Filed, Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense. Court finds CAUSE to adjourn the preliminary hearing. Case is adjourned to Br. 29.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jordin D Curry in court.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case set for a preliminary hearing.  Matter held via Zoom video conference and streamed through DAcast. The defendant requests time to look into hiring their own attorney. Court finds CAUSE to adjourn the preliminary hearing and sets matter for a status of counsel hearing in Branch 29.  This hearing may be streamed live at the discretion of the Court via https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/c105c3fe-89b8-5d05-5f8c-b6cf0d4921da  Status conference scheduled for July 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Oral No Contact Order: Defendant ordered she can have contact with her children pursuant to any CPS orders in place. Court advises that if the CPS orders have expired or are no longer in effect at this time, this reverts to a NO VIOLENT contact order with her children.

Defendant Jordin D Curry in court with attorney Heather L. Johnson.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kiefer, Branch 29.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT DOES NOT QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch 29.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 7, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
